21. A steerable sheath comprising:
a handle including a housing, a port formed on the housing, and a user input wheel rotatably coupled to the housing;
a sheath extending from the handle, the sheath includes a proximal end coupled to the handle and a distal end;
a transmission coupled between the user input wheel and the distal end of the sheath;
wherein actuation of the user input wheel articulates the distal end of the sheath.

31. The sheath of claim 21, wherein the transmission includes:
a drive gear;
a belt coupled between the user input wheel and the drive gear;
a first rack enmeshed with the drive gear;
a second rack enmeshed with the drive gear; and
a first pull wire coupled to the first rack;
